reviews.text: The Paine House Is A Great  Experience! I am a A Member . You should all check it out for a tour.
Lovely but odd
Historical home build circa 1680. DJ is a great tour guide.

I work at the Paine House, I do the inventroy, clean, do tours, and lots more. The president of the Western RI Civic Historical Society trusts me the most in the house. So if you have questions email me, my email is on my profile.
Very haunted
Been going here since I was 3 and I'm now 44, still great

First time I have ever been there. Andthey are so friendly!!! You walk in they automatically great you with how are you. They make you feel so welcomed.  The associate even offered to help me carry the pizza to my car because I was holding my toddler. Amazing!!! I will defiantly be back to get stuff from here.
Great pizza strips and friendly fast service.
Some of the best pizza around. Calzones , pizza strips and hot pizza. All fresh and delicious.
Beware: sold me old stale pizza strips claiming they were fresh. Shame!!!

Imagine fighting your way through winter storm, 100 km on foot. You had to fight your way through a pack of savage penguins and their boss leader, the polar bear, to the bitter end. You open the door after all your struggle into an oasis ice cream, awful awfuls, and traditional American fare. You think you were safe...but in the shadows a monster lurks. You let your guard down, and you order your food happy and content ...but the feeling that something is watching you slowly creeps down your spine. The monster exposes itself as a manager that has an attitude of the most heinous creature in all the land. Your Oasis is ruined... On top of this they have some how figured out how to take flavor out of food and replace it with salt/grease.

This was basically my experience with this Newport creamery. The ice cream was good but the manager at this location it's probably the worst person in customer service I've ever experienced in New England... You can tell the staff is unorganized because of her toxic leadership. I strongly recommend restructuring your management group to better facilitate a well running and friendly staff.

2 stars for quality ice cream though...
Slow staff,  burger was overcooked and dry fries were cold.  Manager did not care.  Will never come here again.

Newport Creamery is a decent place with average food but good people.  We go there mainly for breakfast because it's local, fast, hot, inexpensive, and filling.  That being said, the quality of ingredients is average, not bad but not impressive.  Basically it's an ice cream shop with a diner attached, that de-emphasized their ice cream.  IMHO, they are doing too many things to do anything really well.  It's decent enough food at a decent price, and you can take the kids.
Had our first Big Beef the Creamery Way in over 16 yes & it was like really coming home, DELISH!!
Always great! Servers are wonderful.

The food is very good! The only crab rangoons that I have had with actual chunks of crab meat and boneless spare ribs that are not an artificial pink. Excellent good that we were very happy with, eating in and as delivery. 
Service though leaves a lot to be desired. I believe it is a new restaurant, so maybe they are still working or the kinks? 7pm on NYE and a mostly empty dining room and still slow service. Friendly though.
I'd rather have great food which is why I still give it 4 stars.

Absolutely terrible. We ordered online and waited 2 hours before we finally called, and they told us they didn't get it. Then we ordered again and he said he would call me back when the boss came back, we waited ANOTHER 30 minutes and then called, and he said it was ready and he was on his  way. (We live 3 minutes away). The food arrives 30 minutes later, missing a $14 sushi roll. So once again I call and he says the sushi bar is down, and if we wanted to come in he would give us cash for it, if not there's "nothing he can do".

The owner tried charging us for something they did not give to us. Oh, and btw, they said we ordered “too much food” before they went in the back to make it. It was my wife and I. We were sharing (what would have been 4 rolls). I felt so bad for the waitress, she was doing everything she could, yet the douchebag owner would keep yelling at her and glaring at her. He wouldn’t let her talk to us. This place is terrible and we will NEVER be returning. Creepy place. Cold, out dated. Food is mediocre at best. Don’t waste your money.

Honestly THE best Chinese restaurant I have ever been to. First I could taste the difference...obviously the freshest veggies used. Secondly everything we ordered was cooked to perfection. There was no skimping on flavor or portion size. Top bill in my book. Definitely we will be returning. Be warned...if you do come and see for yourself what I am describing....you will be amazed and hooked.
It's good but not good you feel?

The staff there are the greatest they treat everyone like family you can see they love what they do. They will make your food just the way you want it so good!!!! It's like coming home I just love them.

The Cozy Grill is a great spot to stop and grab a delicious hot breakfast. It is one of my favorite breakfast spots hands down. The staff is friendly and accommodating. The service is quick & the food is always hot. Definitely recommend!
Great food and great people. I haven't had a bad meal here... Ever!
Great breakfast! Everything was delicious. Service was great! The only thing that needs improvement is the coffee. I like strong coffee. But if you don’t, then it’s perfect!

Went in for breakfast recently with my husband and felt compelled to write a review about the fantastic food and service!  The waitstaff was awesome and very attentive.   The food was incredible and the portions were plentiful!  The eggs were cooked to perfection.   I will definitely make the Cozy Grill a regular stop on my breakfast list!!
Good taco pizza and right by the house.  They even have calzones, which seem to be a rarity in Coventry, RI.
Super excellent pizza!! We order from here all of the time. Customer service is great!! The owner is really nice!!
Pizza not very tasty, good thing we got toppings. I asked for roasted red peppers, didn't get them, got regular green peppers.  Lady was pretty crabby.
The owner threw the pizza down in front of me and when I said"charming" she proceeded to take the pizza back and ordered me out!  Charming!
not so good, we had new york system hot dogs, flavor wasnt bad but the rolls were rather stale
Best Pizza in Coventry. Very Fresh Ingredients.
